<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-01-12T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-01-12T09:00:00-05:00" n="211" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d211">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/2426: Telegram (part air)</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-01-12T15:00:00+01:00">January 12, 1935—3
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received January 14—6:27 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>9. Peru has formally notified Secretary General of the nonratification by
                            Colombia within the delay stipulated by article 9 of the Rio de Janeiro
                            protocol of May, 1934, in execution of the Geneva accord of March
                            1933.</p>
                        <p>The Colombian position is not clear to the League authorities. The
                            presumption is that Bogotá will make some statement in reply.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>